Synopsis:
   set status_chanop [<text>]

Description:
   This variable sets the string displayed in the status bar when the user
   is a channel operator in the current channel.  If the user is not a
   channel operator, nothing is displayed.

   This string is represented as %@ in the STATUS_FORMAT string.  It is
   taken literally in STATUS_CHANOP, and has no special meaning.

Examples:
   Customizing the channel operator status indicator:
      /set status_chanop @

See Also:
   mode(1); set(4) status_format, status_voice

